xxl.core.indexStructures

Class SortBasedBulkLoading

  • java.lang.Object
    • xxl.core.indexStructures.SortBasedBulkLoading

  • public class SortBasedBulkLoading
extends Object
    This class provides functionality to bulk-load different types of trees. The tree is created buttom-up.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      protected Function determineContainer
      A Function determining into which container a node is saved.
      protected boolean isMTree
      A flag indicating if tree is an MTree.
      protected Predicate overflows
      A predicate determining if a node overflows (and i.e. a new node has to be allocated).
      protected ArrayList path
      An ArrayList containing the path of nodes in the tree where insertions take place, i.e. the right edge of the tree.
      protected ORTree tree
      The tree which is bulk-loaded.

      • SortBasedBulkLoading

        public SortBasedBulkLoading(ORTree tree,
                            Iterator objects,
                            Function determineContainer)
        Creates a new SortBasedBulkLoading and bulk loads the given tree with the given objects. The predicate overflows of the tree is used to determine when a node overflows.
        Parameters:
        tree - the empty ORtree to bulk-load
        objects - sorted iterator of the objects to be loaded into the tree
        determineContainer - a function determining into which container nodes are saved
